	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2845><span id=Scholar>Jarnin the Wise</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>310 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The limit is actually 127, and I'll tell you why.<br>In everquest, the packets you're sending and recieving have 256 bits of information. The first and last bit of info is used as a header and ender, leaving you with 254. Half of 254 = 127.<br><br>It's my guess that item Hitpoints and Mana are using the same 254 bit info to determine the hp and mana amounts on items. That's why the limit is 127.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
